                    <span>Al Franken shows the lies that neo conservative tries to feed the public as true. His portrayal of the Sean Hannity is right on the mark. He is a rude ken doll that often lies and Colmes is his "liberal" side kick that says one liners and adds nothing to the show other then being the token liberal. I am a libertarian and I agree that neo conservatives like Hannity give conservatives a bad name. I love the chapter on the neo conservative Jesus. That is a hoot.  Like the messed up sermon on the mound, where the neo con Jesus claims that It is easier for the ricj man to come to heaven, then the poor man. This is a sham since Jesus stood up for the poor and the hated. I am old school conservative which means that I believe in small government, personal freedom and social responsibility. It does not mean greed, self importance and pride which seems to be the hallmark of the conservative ideas and ideals presented by people like Limbaugh and Hannity. I think that Franken is a very smart and astute thinker and even though he is a liberal, yes he too loves America.</span>
                  
